<div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />at the default hue setting, color 6 appears more orangy than red, which is why the PAL NES uses a hue of minus 15.<br /></div><br />Actually, the PAL NES appears to use -15 because the official signal spec for PAL uses color bursts separated by 90 degrees at 135 and 225, but because the NES can't output hues 15 degrees off, it uses 150 and 240, which the TV interprets as 135 and 225 and then shifts everything by -15.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Feb 09, 2006 8:50 pm</p><hr />
