<title type="html"><![CDATA[NTSC NES Composite Video Levels]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1071&amp;p=9363#p9363"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />The NES does not produce "pure RGB", as said previously.<br /></div><br /><br />I never said that it did. I'm saying that it was presumably designed such that "red emphasis" was intended to produce a hue that resulted in pure red, that "green emphasis" would produce a pure green hue, and that "blue emphasis" would give a pure blue hue - in other words, based on the assumption that red, green, and blue were each exactly 120 degrees apart from each other, which is clearly <strong>not</strong> the case with YIQ and YUV decoding (in which red-&gt;yellow-&gt;green is 137.26 degrees, green-&gt;cyan-&gt;blue is 106.36 degrees, and blue-&gt;magenta-&gt;red is 116.38 degrees).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Feb 09, 2006 4:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
