<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1071&amp;p=9359#p9359"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NTSC NES Composite Video Levels]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1071&amp;p=9359#p9359"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />The color emphasis bits attenuate based on the phases of $x4, $x8 and $xC, not 2, 6 and A, according to the NTSC Video wiki page, which has been reproduced in my algorithm as well.<br /></div><br /><br />Blue de-emphasis (bit 7) darkens phase 8 which, when applied to white, results in phase 2 (Blue) appearing.<br />Green de-emphasis (bit 6) darkens phase 4 which emphasizes phase A (Green).<br />Red de-emphasis (bit 5) darkens phase C which emphasizes phase 6 (Red).<br /><br />My calculations are based on the naive assumption that the color de-emphasis bits were meant to produce pure R/G/B when applied to white (with the proper hue adjustment) - clearly, this is not the case.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Feb 09, 2006 3:39 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
