<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Actually, from what I've seen, the Saturation technically *should* be "nesLuma[level][1] - nesLuma[level][0]" - the amplitude of the Chroma signal, which should THEN be scaled by userSaturationSetting.<br /></div>That's just another way of describing things. nesChroma [level] = (nesLuma00 [level] - nesLuma0d [level])*0.5. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> Don't forget the 0.5. This is probably even better, because blargg's chroma [4] post still has the amplitudes scaled by 1.27, which was not right, as he said.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=133">NewRisingSun</a> — Thu Feb 09, 2006 2:49 pm</p><hr />
